| Notes                   = * The film was originally scheduled for a January 13, 2023 release.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.thewrap.com/aaron-taylor-johnson-kraven-the-hunter-sony-spider-man-villain-movie/|title=Aaron Taylor-Johnson to Play Spider-Man Villain Kraven the Hunter in Solo Movie|work=The Wrap|last=Verhoeven|first=Beatrice|date=May 26, 2021|accessdate=May 26, 2021}} It was later pushed back to October 6, 2023.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://deadline.com/2022/09/sony-kraven-the-hunter-madame-web-karate-kid-1235121120/|title= New ‘Karate Kid’ Movie Among Sony Pictures Release Date Adds; ‘Kraven The Hunter,’ ‘Madame Web’ Move & More|work= Deadline|last= D'Alessandro|first= Anthony|date= September 16, 2022|accessdate= September 16, 2022}} It would later be pushed back again, to August 30, 2024, due to the {{WP|2023 Hollywood labor disputes|2023 Writers & Actors Strikes}}.{{cite|ref=true|url= https://variety.com/2023/film/news/spider-man-beyond-the-spider-verse-kraven-release-date-pushed-2024-strikes-1235682520/|title= ‘Beyond the Spider-Verse’ Taken Off Sony Release Calendar as Strikes Delay ‘Kraven’ and ‘Ghostbusters’ Sequel to 2024|work= Deadline|last= Donnelly|first= Matt|date= July 28, 2023|accessdate= July 30, 2023}}
* According to the official movie synopsis, [[Peter Parker (Earth-688B)|Spider-Man]] was seemingly set to confront Kraven at some point.<ref>[https://www.kravenmovie.com/synopsis/ Kraven the Hunter official synopsis]</ref> Spider-Man's mention was later removed, however the Red Band trailer for the film and Imagine Engine's portfolio still mentions his involvement.<ref name="Synopsis">[https://youtu.be/rze8QYwWGMs KRAVEN THE HUNTER – Official Red Band Trailer (HD)]</ref><ref name="IE">[https://image-engine.com/portfolio/kraven-the-hunter/ ''Kraven the Hunter'' - Image Engine]</ref>

